The paper deals with decoding LDPC codes over DMCs, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of expectation propagation and the imposition of pairwise marginal constraints are techniques commonly used in machine learning and signal processing, which are subfields of computer science. Therefore, the paper could also belong to the sub-categories of networked systems (cs.NI), social and information networks (cs.SI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and machine learning (cs.LG).
